# {{.ProjectName}}

Codex runtime scaffold generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/plugin-kit-ai/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

This lane models repo-local Codex notify integration, separate from the official Codex plugin bundle.

## Status

- Runtime: `go`
- Lane: `codex-runtime`
- Status: `production-ready`, stable default path
- Bootstrap contract: Go `1.22+`

## First Run

```bash
go test ./...
go build -o bin/{{.ProjectName}} ./cmd/{{.ProjectName}}
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform codex-runtime --strict
{{.Entrypoint}} notify '{"client":"codex-tui"}'
```

The scaffold consumes `github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai/sdk@v1.0.3` as a normal Go module release.

## Stable Default

- `Notify`

The scaffold wires the documented stable Codex `notify` path.

## Target Files

- `launcher.yaml`: runtime and entrypoint for local notify integration
- `targets/codex-runtime/package.yaml`: authored Codex runtime metadata
- `.codex/config.toml`: rendered managed Codex config

Keep stdout reserved for Codex responses and write diagnostics to stderr only.
